    "headline_finding": "BLAST RADIUS SATURATES. At 3 hops both compromised and ordinary identities reach essentially every host in the network (14,256 vs 14,253 of 14,540), so the measure carries no information at that depth. The cause is visible in choke_points_top: hub hosts here are authenticated to by tens of thousands of distinct identities, which collapses the graph into a small world where almost everyone is two hops from almost everyone. Only the 1-hop measure discriminates \u2014 and even that is confounded, because the accounts the red team chose to compromise were higher-privilege to begin with. The genuinely actionable output of this stage is therefore not blast radius but the choke points: harden those hubs and you break the paths.",
